{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3660", "repo": "rails", "body": "@jdelStrother Hm, you might be right.  I was generating an RSS feed that was read by Mailchimp and sent to people.  The rss feed contained URLs of images that used relative protocols -- so the html emails people received had images that used relative protocols and that caused problems (Outlook wouldn't show the email at all, iPhone wouldn't display the images).\r\n\r\nSo yeah, in my case ActionMailer wasn't at fault.  I fixed the problem by doing\r\n\r\n```\r\nconfig.action_controller.default_asset_host_protocol = nil\r\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "523833d0bd3543c15100fa97"}, "issue_id": 3660, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2809158", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3660#issuecomment-2809158", "updated_at": "2011-11-20T22:50:55Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk", "login": "joevandyk", "gravatar_id": "e1c881ecb7bf966f44fecaa5387ab26b", "html_url": "https://github.com/joevandyk", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/e1c881ecb7bf966f44fecaa5387ab26b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdabd8d2ce74e782c65a973ef76fd540b.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1179, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/joevandyk/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-11-20T22:50:55Z", "id": 2809158, "owner": "rails"}
